cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of automated segmentation of the prostate from 3D MR images using deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model also involves domain adaptation and transfer learning, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of MR images also suggests the subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of insufficient training data, which can be addressed using techniques from neural networks (cs.NE).
